The paper deals with the recovery of sparse signals from noisy measurements, which is a common problem in signal processing and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are the most likely categories. The paper also uses compressed sensing theory, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of a specific algorithm, which could be considered under cs.SI (Sound and Image Processing).
